About
=====
Two libraries:

- formula: for manipulating formula and expressions involving
  Boolean, enumerated, bounded integer variables, and numerical expressions,
  using BDDs and MTBDDs.

- bddDomain: abstract domains combining Boolean and Numerical 
  variables using APRON library

Required
========
C  libraries: 
  GMP (http://gmplib.org)
  MPFR (http://www.mpfr.org/)
  CUDD (http://vlsi.colorado.edu/~fabio/CUDD/)
  cuddaux (http://gforge.inria.fr/projects/mlxxxidl/)
  APRON (http://apron.cri.ensmp.fr/library/)
	(optional, if you do not use some modules)
C/OCaml libraries
  mlgmpidl, mlcuddidl (http://gforge.inria.fr/projects/mlxxxidl/)
OCaml libraries
  camllib (http://gforge.inria.fr/projects/bjeannet/)

To configure
============
- copy Makefile.config.model into Makefile.config
- set properly the flags (mainly directories).

To compile the library:
=======================
make all # for bytecode and nativecode compilation of formula
make formula # idem
make bddDomain # for bytecode and nativecode compilation of bddDomain

To install the library:
=======================
make install
